        "renderShape": {
          "kind": "markdown"
        },
        "markdown": "# Handle / Port Binding Smoke\n\nUse this graph to verify that semantic ports drive edges, while handles remain the visible interaction points around those ports."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "handle-port-binding-smoke-guide",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "How To Test",
      "root": true,
      "position": {
        "x": 40,
        "y": -260
      },
      "width": 760,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-basic-primitives-handle-port-binding-smoke"
        },
        "markdown": "# Handle / Port Binding Smoke Test\n\nThis graph demonstrates the current contract:\n- `ports` are the semantic interface\n- `sourcePort` and `targetPort` stay canonical on edges\n- multiple handles may bind to the same semantic port\n- a handle with no `portId` remains visual-only and should not create a connection\n\n## Authoring note\nIn the current properties-panel flow, adding a new handle usually creates a matching semantic port at the same time.\n\nThis smoke graph goes one level deeper than that authoring shortcut so you can inspect the underlying binding model directly.\n\n## What is wired here\n- `Source Node` exposes semantic ports `root` and `message`\n- `Source Node` has **two bound handles** for the `message` port: `message-east` and `message-south`\n- `Source Node` also has one **visual-only** handle: `decoy`\n- `Receiver Node` exposes semantic ports `root` and `message`\n- `Receiver Node` has one bound input handle and one visual-only badge handle\n\n## Smoke checks\n1. Select `Source Node` and inspect **Handles**.\n2. Confirm `message-east` and `message-south` both bind to port `message`.\n3. Confirm `decoy` is visual-only.\n4. Notice the existing edge from `Source Node` to `Receiver Node` uses `sourcePort = message` and `targetPort = message`.\n5. Verify both bound source handles look connected, while `decoy` does not.\n6. Delete the edge and recreate it by dragging from either bound source handle to the receiver handle.\n7. Confirm the recreated edge still uses the semantic port id `message`.\n8. Try dragging from `decoy` or the receiver `badge`. They should not create a connection."
      }
    },
